Traditional sensors always face the challenge of identifying multiple TCs, especially mixed TCs. To evaluate the ability of the ratiometric fluorescent probe based on N/S-CQDs and TGA-CdTe QDs to recognize various TCs, samples including a single TC, two TCs mixed and three TCs mixed were all tested. As shown in Fig. 3
                        A, with the aid of the linear discriminant analysis (LDA) model, each sample, even the mixture of two or three TCs, could be clearly separated from each other without obvious overlap, which further showed the potential application of the novel ratiometric fluorescent probe in the analysis of complex mixed samples. Compared with our previous report, our novel probe was comparable to or better than other sensing methods, especially in detecting different TCs (Table 1
                        ).
